# https://cdm.ovh/rsm/topology/topo#connectedWith
<https://cdm.ovh/rsm/topology/topo#connectedWith> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#ObjectProperty> .
<https://cdm.ovh/rsm/topology/topo#connectedWith> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#subPropertyOf> <https://cdm.ovh/rsm/topology/topo#connectedWithTransitive> .
<https://cdm.ovh/rsm/topology/topo#connectedWith> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#SymmetricProperty> .
<https://cdm.ovh/rsm/topology/topo#connectedWith> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "connected with"@en .
<https://cdm.ovh/rsm/topology/topo#connectedWith> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> "Relation between a port on a net element and the adjacent port on another net element. This is a symmetric relation. Geographic locations of related ports may not coincide, either because of constructive tolerances (abutted tracks...), or uncertainties, or rounding errors, or by construction (e.g. case of tracks joined via a turntable)."@en .
# 
# https://cdm.ovh/rsm/topology/topo#connectedWithTransitive
<https://cdm.ovh/rsm/topology/topo#connectedWithTransitive> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#ObjectProperty> .
<https://cdm.ovh/rsm/topology/topo#connectedWithTransitive> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#TransitiveProperty> .
<https://cdm.ovh/rsm/topology/topo#connectedWithTransitive> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#domain> <https://cdm.ovh/rsm/topology/topo#Port> .
<https://cdm.ovh/rsm/topology/topo#connectedWithTransitive> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#range> <https://cdm.ovh/rsm/topology/topo#Port> .
<https://cdm.ovh/rsm/topology/topo#connectedWithTransitive> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "connected with transitive"@en .
<https://cdm.ovh/rsm/topology/topo#connectedWithTransitive> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> "transitive closure of connectedWith."@en .
# 
