_:genid2 <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#first> <https://cdm.ovh/rsm/topology/topo#onElement> .
_:genid2 <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#List> .
_:genid3 <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#first> <https://cdm.ovh/rsm/topology/topo#navigableTo> .
_:genid3 <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#List> .
_:genid4 <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#first> <https://cdm.ovh/rsm/topology/topo#port> .
_:genid4 <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#List> .
<https://cdm.ovh/rsm/topology/topo#leadsTo> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "leads to"@en .
<https://cdm.ovh/rsm/topology/topo#leadsTo> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> "relation between two adjacent net elements (i.e. having connected ports), where rolling stock can start moving from the first and arrive on the second without reversing travel direction. This property is not symmetric (think of sprung switches). A shortcut property for reasoning directly on net elements."@en .
# 
# https://cdm.ovh/rsm/topology/topo#leadsToTransitive
<https://cdm.ovh/rsm/topology/topo#leadsToTransitive> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#ObjectProperty> .
<https://cdm.ovh/rsm/topology/topo#leadsToTransitive> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#TransitiveProperty> .
<https://cdm.ovh/rsm/topology/topo#leadsToTransitive> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#domain> <https://cdm.ovh/rsm/topology/topo#NetElement> .
<https://cdm.ovh/rsm/topology/topo#leadsToTransitive> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#range> <https://cdm.ovh/rsm/topology/topo#NetElement> .
