_:genid6 <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#first> <https://cdm.ovh/rsm/topology/topo#navigableToTransitive> .
_:genid6 <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#List> .
_:genid7 <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#first> <https://cdm.ovh/rsm/topology/topo#port> .
_:genid7 <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#List> .
<https://cdm.ovh/rsm/topology/topo#leadsToTransitive> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "technical note: this may look like, but is *not* the transitive closure of leadsTo. The transitive closure of leadsTo would include train movements with reversal of travel direction, which is not desirable."@en .
<https://cdm.ovh/rsm/topology/topo#leadsToTransitive> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "leads to transitive"@en .
<https://cdm.ovh/rsm/topology/topo#leadsToTransitive> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> "relation between net elements (adjacent or not), where rolling stock may leave the first (subject) and reach the second (object) without reversing travel direction."@en .
