<https://cdm.ovh/rsm/adapters/geosparql_adapter/geo_ad#hasNominalMetricLength> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#domain> <https://cdm.ovh/rsm/topology/topology#LinearElement> .
<https://cdm.ovh/rsm/adapters/geosparql_adapter/geo_ad#hasNominalMetricLength> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#range> <http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#double> .
<https://cdm.ovh/rsm/adapters/geosparql_adapter/geo_ad#hasNominalMetricLength> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "has nominal metric length"@en .
<https://cdm.ovh/rsm/adapters/geosparql_adapter/geo_ad#hasNominalMetricLength> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> "This length is assumed to be derived from the chosen Nominal Geometry.\n\nThe Nominal Metric Length is supposed to be used for conversions between linear referencing methods \"absolute\" (distance along, e.g. used in CCS/TMS data model) and \"interpolation\" (intrinsic coordinates, with values 0 to 1, used in RSM and others)." .
